[Claude]: This is a critical finding confirmed. All 9 notifiers use `StandardEvaluationContext` (unrestricted) - meaning SpEL expressions can call `T(java.lang.Runtime).getRuntime().exec(...)`. The key question is: **are these SpEL message templates themselves configurable via the Spring Boot application properties that could be influenced by a registered instance?**

